, "small": {"faces": [{"h": 73, "w": 73, "x": 133, "y": 493}, {"h": 85, "w": 85, "x": 368, "y": 488}]}}, "id_str": "2073171453130715136", "indices": [273, 296], "media_key": "3_2073171453130715136", "media_results": {"result": {"media_key": "3_2073171453130715136"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HMVic9ZWMAAfz0i.png", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 409, "w": 731, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 651, "w": 651, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 651, "w": 571, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 651, "w": 326, "x": 0, "y": 0}, {"h": 651, "w": 731, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 651, "width": 731}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 651, "resize": "fit", "w": 731}, "medium": {"h": 651, "resize": "fit", "w": 731}, "small": {"h": 606, "resize": "fit", "w": 680}, "thumb": {"h": 150, "resize": "crop", "w": 150}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/G9BLqsYoyC"}, {"allow_download_status": {"allow_download": true}, "display_url": "pic.x.com/G9BLqsYoyC", "expanded_url": "https://x.com/stockzandstuff/status/2073171594264850523/photo/1", "ext_media_availability": {"status": "Available"}, "features": {"large": {"faces": []}, "medium": {"faces": []}, "orig": {"faces": []}, "small": {"faces": []}}, "id_str": "2073171452530950144", "indices": [273, 296], "media_key": "3_2073171452530950144", "media_results": {"result": {"media_key": "3_2073171452530950144"}}, "media_url_https": "https://pbs.twimg.com/media/HMVic7KWgAAV5e8.png", "original_info": {"focus_rects": [{"h": 228, "w": 407, "x": 0, "y": 55}, {"h": 283, "w": 283, "x": 11, "y": 0}, {"h": 283, "w": 248, "x": 28, "y": 0}, {"h": 283, "w": 142, "x": 81, "y": 0}, {"h": 283, "w": 407, "x": 0, "y": 0}], "height": 283, "width": 407}, "sizes": {"large": {"h": 283, "resize": "fit", "w": 407}, "medium": {"h": 283, "resize": "fit", "w": 407}, "small": {"h": 283, "resize": "fit", "w": 407}, "thumb": {"h": 150, "resize": "crop", "w": 150}}, "type": "photo", "url": "https://t.co/G9BLqsYoyC"}]}, "favorite_count": 0, "favorited": false, "full_text": "$STM, STMicroelectronics. STM is one of Europe's largest chipmakers, and it builds its own chips end-to-end, from design all the way through its own factories. Its parts are the unglamorous but essential pieces inside almost everything — the sensors, power chips, and tiny https://t.co/G9BLqsYoyC", "id_str": "2073171594264850523", "is_quote_status": false, "lang": "en", "possibly_sensitive": true, "possibly_sensitive_editable": true, "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 0, "retweet_count": 0, "retweeted": false, "user_id_str": "1168282976653926400"}, "note_tweet": {"is_expandable": true, "note_tweet_results": {"result": {"entity_set": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [0, 4], "text": "STM"}], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNzMxNzE1OTQwMjE1ODA4MDA=", "media": {"inline_media": []}, "richtext": {"richtext_tags": [{"from_index": 1225, "richtext_types": ["Bold"], "to_index": 1233}]}, "text": "$STM, STMicroelectronics. STM is one of Europe's largest chipmakers, and it builds its own chips end-to-end, from design all the way through its own factories. Its parts are the unglamorous but essential pieces inside almost everything — the sensors, power chips, and tiny "brains" (microcontrollers) inside cars, phones, factory machines, satellites, robots, and now AI data centers.

What makes STM unique is the sheer breadth: it holds a #1 or #2 position in an unusual number of separate chip categories at once (SiC power, MEMS sensors, STM32 microcontrollers), which lets a customer like NVIDIA source a whole system — sensors, brain, power, and communications — from one vendor. The reason it's suddenly interesting is that a company written off for two years as a "sleepy automotive chipmaker" just found a real AI growth engine: on June 2 it doubled its 2026 data-center revenue target to ~$1B (with a path to ~$2B in 2027), anchored by a multi-year AWS silicon-photonics deal, while sitting on ~$2.8B net cash. The investment case is a cyclical turnaround (Q1 revenue +23% YoY, up ~90%+ off February lows) layered on top of a genuine new secular driver, with the biggest names in tech — AWS, NVIDIA — as partners.

Thesis: STM spent two years being ignored as a boring car-chip company, but it just quietly turned into an AI company — its parts now go inside Amazon and NVIDIA's data centers, and that business is set to double two years in a row. The stock has already jumped a lot, so the easy money is gone, but the real question is whether its profit margins can climb back to normal as sales recover — if they do, the stock is still cheap for what it's about to earn. I'm watching the July 23 earnings to see if those margins are finally turning up, because that's the part the market hasn't fully believed yet."}}}, "previous_counts": {"bookmark_count": 0, "favorite_count": 0, "quote_count": 0, "reply_count": 0, "retweet_count": 0}, "rest_id": "2073171594264850523", "source": "<a href="https://mobile.twitter.com" rel="nofollow">Twitter Web App</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "102", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}}

